<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Users API</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <style>
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="p-3">
        <h1>Documentation</h1>
        <p>This is a simple REST API about users data. You may access these endpoints to use the API:</p>
        <ul>
            <li class="mb-3">
                <span class="badge text-bg-success">GET</span>
                <a href="/api/users"><code>/api/users</code></a>
                Get all users data
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                <span class="badge text-bg-primary">POST</span>
                <a href="/api/users"><code>/api/users</code></a>
                Create a new user. Body should contain JSON with the following structure.
                <br>
                <div class="mt-3">
                    <span class="bg-dark text-danger font-monospace p-2">
                        {
                            "name": "John Doe",
                            "email": "johndoe@example.com",
                            "age": 30
                        }
                    </span>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                <span class="badge text-bg-success">GET</span>
                <code>/api/users/:id</code>
                Get user data by ID. For example: <code>/api/users/69</code>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                <span class="badge text-bg-warning">PUT</span>
                <code>/api/users/:id</code>
                Update user data with given ID. Body should contain JSON with the following structure.
                <br>
                <div class="mt-3">
                    <span class="bg-dark text-danger font-monospace p-2">
                        {
                            "id": 69,
                            "name": "John Doe",
                            "email": "johndoe@example.com",
                            "age": 30
                        }
                    </span>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-3">
                <span class="badge text-bg-danger">DELETE</span>
                <code>/api/users/:id</code>
                Delete user data with given ID. For example: <code>/api/users/69</code
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
